      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the consistency of KENNYS SON (6) who has placed in all three starts since recording back-to-back wins last month. Finished second from a similar barrier to this at his latest appearance at Melton, beaten 1.7 metres. He is two from two at this distance range and could maintain that perfect record. SPIRITED GIGI (3) settled close to the pace and closed well for a 3m third last start at Melton, that effort coming on the back of a sound third at Maryborough the run before. Has the benefit of a good draw. Building in fitness so could break through. SEBASTIANS WAITING (9) resumes after four-and-a-half months. Manners were hit and miss last time in but he is capable and a trial win suggests he is back in good order. ZOOLU (5) has trialled well since breaking last time. Good enough to feature if she gets it right.",
